NAME
	iris

DESCRIPTION
	Iris micro protects your eyes in under 1MB.
	You can use a default mode (day,night,max), or run iris with custom values.

	For example, `iris 2000 50` sets `temperature` to '2000K' & `brightness` to '50%'

ARGUMENTS
	This function accepts two parameters:
	---------------------------------------

	@1 = temperature 	(degrees in kelvin)	[1 - 10000]
	@2 = brightness  	(percentage)				[1 - 100]

SYNOPSIS
	iris [temperature] [brightness]
	iris [--day,-d || --night,-n || --max,-m]

EXAMPLES
	iris					# auto
	iris 2000 50	# dimmer, warmer
	iris 6000 95	# brighter, cooler
	iris --day		# set for daytime mode (also valid: `iris day` or `iris -d`)
	iris --night	# set for nighttime mode (also valid: `iris night` or `iris -n`)
	iris --max		# set for maximum temperature & brightness (also valid: `iris max` or `iris -m`)

AVAILABLE OPTIONS:
	--day, -d			[activate daytime settings]
	--night, -n		[activate nighttime settings]
	--max, -m			[activate nighttime settings]
